<Layout title="Course Overview">
  <h1>D442 – Basic Nursing Skills: Course Overview</h1>

  <h2>Course Description</h2>
  <p>
    Basic Nursing Skills introduces foundational principles of the nursing process and the
    clinical judgment model, health assessment techniques, and communication skills for
    diverse adult patients across the lifespan. Skills focus on vital signs, medication
    administration, infection control, nutrition, elimination, mobility, oxygenation, and
    skin integrity.
  </p>
  <div class="warning">
    <strong>⚠️ Important</strong>
    Students must be successful on lab assessments to progress to Adult Health I clinical.
  </div>
  <p>
    <strong>Co-requisites:</strong> D443 – Health Assessment; D444 – Adult Health I<br />
    <strong>Prerequisite:</strong> All prelicensure nursing curriculum courses from previous terms.
  </p>

  <h2>Course Competencies</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>#</th><th>Competency</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>7093.4.1</td><td>Performs Health Assessments – performs health assessment strategies and techniques on diverse adult patients to gather information</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.2</td><td>Develops a Care Plan – develops a plan of care using the nursing process and clinical judgment model</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.3</td><td>Demonstrates Sterile Techniques for Infection Control</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.4</td><td>Demonstrates Daily Personal Hygiene Practices</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.5</td><td>Performs Supportive Assistance for Mobility Needs</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.6</td><td>Performs Nutritional Support Interventions</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.7</td><td>Demonstrates Oxygenation Techniques</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.8</td><td>Performs Medication Administration</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.9</td><td>Performs Elimination Requirements</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.10</td><td>Collects Specimens</td></tr>
      <tr><td>7093.4.11</td><td>Applies Nursing Process/Clinical Judgment Model</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Course Assessments</h2>
  <p>These are the <strong>required assessments</strong> to demonstrate competency:</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Basic Nursing Skills Pre-Lab HESI Patient Review</strong> – must score 80%+, due <em>two weeks before</em> first lab day</li>
    <li><strong>Basic Nursing Skills Pre-Lab Shadow Health Digital Clinical Experience (DCE)</strong> – must score 80%+, due two weeks before first lab day</li>
    <li><strong>Basic Nursing Skills On Ground Lab</strong> – Performance Assessment; must pass to progress to D444 Adult Health I Clinical Intensive</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Ticket to Ride (Required Before Lab)</h2>
  <p>
    You <strong>must complete and pass all of the following with 80% or higher, two weeks
    prior to the first lab day</strong> to be eligible to attend the D442 Basic Nursing
    Skills Intensive Lab.
  </p>
  <h3>Shadow Health Digital Clinical Experiences (DCE)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Gerontology: Pain (Edward Carter)</li>
    <li>Gerontology: Mobility (Robert Hall)</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>HESI Patient Reviews</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Clinical Nursing Concepts – Dave Mason</li>
    <li>Adult Health/Respiratory Health Problems – Mr. Hannigan</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Learning Resources</h2>
  <h3>Primary Textbooks (included in tuition)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Potter Fundamentals of Nursing – Sherpath for Fundamentals, 11th Edition</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Touhy Gerontologic Nursing and Healthy Aging, 6th Edition</strong></li>
  </ul>

