  <h2>Platforms &amp; Resources</h2>

  <h3>VitalSource</h3>
  <p>
    eTexts are available as part of program tuition. Create a VitalSource account with your
    WGU email (<code>username@wgu.edu</code>).
  </p>

  <h3>Sherpath (Elsevier)</h3>
  <p>Personalized teaching and learning platform with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Essential Lessons</strong> – interactive digital lessons</li>
    <li><strong>Expanded Readings</strong> – linked to Elsevier eBooks</li>
    <li><strong>Elsevier Adaptive Quizzes (EAQ)</strong> – adaptive quizzing for self-assessment</li>
    <li><strong>Enrichment Activities</strong> (not required, but highly recommended)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>SimChart</h3>
  <p>
    Simulated Electronic Health Record (EHR) for electronic charting practice. Access
    SimChart Case Studies through My Evolve. <em>(Enrichment only — not required)</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Clinical Skills</h3>
  <p>
    Seven-part framework for each nursing skill including quick sheet, extended text, supply
    lists, videos, and documentation guidelines. Use to print checklists and practice with
    SimuMED kit.
  </p>

  <h3>HESI</h3>
  <p>
    Provides practice exams, case studies, and patient reviews to prepare for NCLEX.
    Product includes: HESI Patient Reviews, Case Studies, Practice Exams.
  </p>

  <h3>Shadow Health</h3>
  <p>
    Virtual reality simulation for practicing patient assessments. Scores are sent directly
    to WGU. Technical support: <strong>1-800-860-3241</strong>.
  </p>

  <h3>SimuMED</h3>
  <p>Physical simulation kit received at program enrollment. Contents:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Acrylic Stand, Male/Female/Face Pieces</li>
    <li>Deep Wound + Stand, Central Line</li>
    <li>Tracheostomy Tube, Stoma Simulator</li>
    <li>Injection Pad (adjustable arm/leg), IV Training Pad</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Simulation Learning System (SLS)</h3>
  <p>
    Elsevier's SLS guides preparation for in-person simulation labs. Access via Evolve using
    course ID: <strong>154359_dswanson86_1001</strong>
  </p>

  <h2>Course Navigation Tips</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use <strong>Chrome</strong> (preferred) or <strong>Firefox</strong> (acceptable). Do NOT use Safari, MS Explorer, or Edge.</li>
    <li>Course uses links to direct you to content. Complete content elements as indicated, then return to the course to continue.</li>
    <li>Knowledge checks (EAQs) are not predictive of assessment format.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Lab Intensive Preparation</h2>
  <p>
    The LSH Nursing Learning Lab provides a risk-free environment that reinforces clinical
    judgment, promotes patient safety, and improves communication and efficiency in clinical
    settings.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Before attending lab, you must:</strong></p>
  <ol>
    <li>Complete your <strong>Ticket to Ride</strong> requirements (see above)</li>
    <li>Review the <strong>Clinical Skills</strong> for each lab skill and <strong>print the checklists</strong> (from the Checklist tab → Print Checklist button)</li>
    <li>Practice using your <strong>SimuMED kit</strong></li>
  </ol>
</Layout>
